Purpose
This smoke checklist is intended to confirm that the application build is stable enough for further testing. 
It focuses on core functionality and major risk areas rather than deep edge-case or full regression coverage.

Exit Guidance
If all critical checks pass, proceed to deeper functional, exploratory, or regression testing.
If one or more critical checks fail, pause further testing and log defects before continuing.

Status Legend
Pass — Check completed successfully.
Fail — Check completed and did not meet expected result.
Blocked — Check could not be completed due to another issue.
Not Run — Check has not yet been executed.

